The paper deals with handwritten text recognition using deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of recurrent layers, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of different models on complex datasets, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques.
